        "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "summary_markdown": "```markdown\n## What this issue is about\nThis issue aims to enhance Plone’s documentation to attract first-time contributors. It's modeled after a similar initiative from the icalendar project, with the goal of making it easier for newcomers to engage with the community.\n\n## What needs to be done\n1. Update the documentation to reflect this pilot program.\n2. Consider including options for low or non-code contributions such as translations, blog posts, and graphic design.\n3. The issue is still open for community input and suggestions.\n\n## Helpful background\nThis initiative has successfully partnered with \"Up for Grabs,\" a platform that helps people find beginner-friendly issues to work on. The mention of \"Good First Issue\" suggests it aims to be easily approachable, though there is uncertainty about its acceptance status.\n\n## Good first steps\n- Review the existing documentation and propose enhancements.\n- Consider how non-code contributions can be integrated into the process.\n- Engage in discussions on the “Good First Issue” and provide feedback or suggestions.\n- Familiarize yourself with the pilot model used by the icalendar project for inspiration.\n```",
